parameters.name: form Optional
parameters.description: An HTML <form> element — when specified, the FormData object will be populated with the form's current keys/values using the name property of each element for the keys and their submitted value for the values. It will also encode file input content.

members.name: FormData.append()
members.description: Appends a new value onto an existing key inside a FormData object, or adds the key if it does not already exist.

parameters.name: name
parameters.description: The name of the field whose data is contained in value.

parameters.name: value
parameters.description: The field's value. This can be a USVString or Blob (including subclasses such as File).

parameters.name: filename Optional
parameters.description: The filename reported to the server (a USVString), when a Blob or File is passed as the second parameter. The default filename for Blob objects is "blob". The default filename for File objects is the file's filename.

members.name: FormData.delete()
members.description: Deletes a key/value pair from a FormData object.

parameters.name: name
parameters.description: The name of the key you want to delete.

members.name: FormData.entries()
members.description: Returns an iterator allowing to go through all key/value pairs contained in this object.

members.name: FormData.get()
members.description: Returns the first value associated with a given key from within a FormData object.

parameters.name: name
parameters.description: A USVString representing the name of the key you want to retrieve.

members.name: FormData.getAll()
members.description: Returns an array of all the values associated with a given key from within a FormData.

parameters.name: name
parameters.description: A USVString representing the name of the key you want to retrieve.

members.name: FormData.has()
members.description: Returns a boolean stating whether a FormData object contains a certain key/value pair.

parameters.name: name
parameters.description: A USVString representing the name of the key you want to test for.

members.name: FormData.keys()
members.description: Returns an iterator allowing to go through all keys of the key/value pairs contained in this object.

members.name: FormData.set()
members.description: Sets a new value for an existing key inside a FormData object, or adds the key/value if it does not already exist.

parameters.name: name
parameters.description: The name of the field whose data is contained in value.

parameters.name: value
parameters.description: The field's value. In the two parameter version this is a USVString, or if it is not, it is converted to a string. In the three parameter version this can be a Blob, File, or a USVString. If none of these are specified the value is converted to a string.

parameters.name: filename Optional
parameters.description: The filename reported to the server (a USVString), when a Blob or File is passed as the second parameter. The default filename for Blob objects is "blob".

members.name: FormData.values()
members.description: Returns an iterator allowing to go through all values of the key/value pairs contained in this object.
